Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:09.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Hello, this video is an introduction of BillardGL.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.50,0:00:13.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,BillardGL is a billiard game on PC-Unix.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.50,0:00:17.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Its graphics using OpenGL is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.00,0:00:22.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I played it on FreeBSD 9.0/amd64.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:26.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,The graphics card was ASUS GT440 with NVIDIA GeForce GT440 GPU.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:31.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Now I start explaining how to play this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.50,0:00:35.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I am at "View" mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:40.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I can swing the camera with dragging the left button of my mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:45.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Dragging the right button horizontally moves the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:51.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Vertical dragging of the right button zooms in/out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.00,0:00:58.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I can aiso zoom in/out with Page Up/Down of a keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.00,0:01:04.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Insert/Delete buttons changes vertical position of the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.00,0:01:09.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Function keys from F1 to F8 change view.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.50,0:01:11.40,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F1
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.40,0:01:13.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F2
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.50,0:01:15.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F3
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.50,0:01:17.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F4
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.50,0:01:20.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F5
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.00,0:01:22.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F6
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.50,0:01:24.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F7
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.50,0:01:27.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,F8
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:36.50,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Cursor keys on the keyboard moves the camera's position.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.00,0:01:42.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I can focus a ball by clicking one of balls at bottom of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.00,0:01:57.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,When you push a space bar, you will be in "Aim" mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.50,0:02:08.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,In Aim mode, view rotates around the white ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:14.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,When you decide direction, press the space bar. Don't release immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.50,0:02:20.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0280,,You will shot on releasing the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:37.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0280,,You can replay the last shot with the "r" key.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:47.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0280,,You can replay as many times as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:59.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,At last, I explain "Place White" mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.50,0:03:08.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0210,,When you drop the white ball, mode will be changed to "Place White" mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:14.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0210,,In this mode, cursor keys can change position of the white ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:24.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,To exit the game, please click the logo at top-left corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.50,0:03:32.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Notice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:38.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0000,,I changed the settings of controls before recording this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:44.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,I inverted X/Y-axis. It is natural for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.50,0:03:50.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,And one more notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:54.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,You must find that some parts in the screen blink.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:58.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,It was a broblem of recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:04:02.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,They did not blink in the actual screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.00,0:04:07.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,My explanation is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:19.00,Games on FreeBSD,,0000,0000,0070,,Danke. Enjoy!
